Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.33,0:03:06.95,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.37,0:03:08.33,Default,S,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.33,0:03:09.16,Default,T,0,0,0,,Thanks for meeting with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.58,0:03:10.04,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Huh—
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.58,0:03:12.50,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I forgot to bring the evaluation reports.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.08,0:03:14.46,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Do you guys mind coming upstairs with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.96,0:03:16.17,Default,S,0,0,0,,Upstairs as in—
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.17,0:03:17.26,Default,T,0,0,0,,Where the editorial department is?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.26,0:03:17.92,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.63,0:03:23.39,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You'll need that badge to get in.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.39,0:03:26.39,Default,S,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's alright for us to come in?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.97,0:03:27.89,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.89,0:03:30.98,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Elementary and middle school kids \Ncome in all the time on field trips.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.23,0:03:36.07,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,I'm so looking forward to seeing \NJack's editorial department!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.71,0:03:52.67,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,This way, you two.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.29,0:03:54.33,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.33,0:03:57.25,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Everyone reacts like that the first \Ntime they get off the elevator.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.42,0:04:00.05,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,And here's the editorial department.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.85,Default,Editor 1,0,0,0,,This is the Shounen Jack's editorial department.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.26,0:04:09.56,Default,Editor 2,0,0,0,,When's the manuscript gonna be finished?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.73,0:04:16.11,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,This is Jack's editorial department!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.11,0:04:17.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,This is pretty incredible!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.40,0:04:18.94,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.40,0:04:21.19,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Let's go to the table over there.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.19,0:04:21.94,Default,S&T,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.11,0:04:27.12,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Your judges were Inagaki-sensei,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.12,0:04:30.95,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Ota-sensei, Toriyama-sensei, Kishimoto-sensei,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.95,0:04:35.17,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Tezuka Productions, Editor in Chief of \NJack SQ, and our own Editor in Chief.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.25,0:04:38.29,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Wait, that man—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.17,0:04:43.55,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,came to my uncle's funeral!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.55,0:04:45.13,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Mashiro, are you listening?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.47,0:04:46.93,Default,S,0,0,0,,Y—Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.55,0:04:52.10,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,The mangakas gave you \Nguys a pretty good evaluation.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.10,0:04:54.10,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,The editors' evaluation weren't so good.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.06,0:04:56.44,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Can you guys guess why?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.31,0:05:00.82,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Because this sort of work wouldn't get \Npublished in Jack. That's how they evaluate it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.32,0:05:06.36,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the artists tend to favor \Nworks that wouldn't get published in Jack.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.70,0:05:09.16,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Probably because they value \Nthe originality of such works.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.78,0:05:13.45,Default,T,0,0,0,,What exactly about it makes it unsuitable for Jack?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.45,0:05:17.83,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That the protagonist is a normal human, just \Nlike in your other work, "The Two Earths."
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.50,0:05:23.34,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,A typical Jack protagonist has \Nflamboyant special abilities.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.34,0:05:26.18,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Of course, all our series can't be like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.40,Default,T,0,0,0,,A normal human—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.40,0:05:30.76,Default,T,0,0,0,,Does it still read like a novel?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.31,0:05:35.39,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Maybe, but that's also part of your style.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.39,0:05:38.48,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,The protagonist is undeniably weak though.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.48,0:05:39.23,Default,S,0,0,0,,Um—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.86,0:05:43.44,Default,S,0,0,0,,Is my art bad?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.36,0:05:46.95,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's not the case at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.95,0:05:50.87,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You got more 4s than 3s on the art.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.87,0:05:52.24,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You still have room for improvement though.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.24,0:05:55.79,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I think they gave you 3s so you'd \Nkeep developing your skills.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.33,0:05:58.75,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You'll keep getting better if you practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.21,0:06:00.33,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,But you're already very good.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.09,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.47,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,I'm not holding Shuujin back.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.30,0:06:09.55,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,These are really impressive scores.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.55,0:06:11.22,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You guys just had bad luck this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.85,0:06:15.43,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,'Cause Niizuma Eiji won \Nfirst prize and runner up.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.31,0:06:19.94,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,You guys would've at least gotten an \Nhonorable mention, if it weren't for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.94,0:06:23.07,Default,T,0,0,0,,This Niizuma Eiji guy's really good—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.86,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,He is. Almost too good to be true.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.86,0:06:28.36,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,They're saying he's one of \Nthose once-a-decade prodigies.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.07,0:06:32.99,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,He actually moved here from Aomori \Nin preparation for serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.99,0:06:33.74,Default,S&T,0,0,0,,Serialization?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.24,0:06:36.12,Default,T,0,0,0,,A high school student can get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.95,0:06:37.79,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,They can.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.54,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Mashiro can probably guess this:
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.54,0:06:47.30,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,How much time would it save if you only drew \Nthe characters and let assistants handle the rest?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.59,0:06:50.43,Default,S,0,0,0,,It could be done in a fourth—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.43,0:06:51.93,Default,S,0,0,0,,No, a fifth of the time!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.93,0:06:54.97,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Right. With assistants, it's doable.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.72,0:07:00.10,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,And Niizuma's been able to submit \Na work by himself every month,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.10,0:07:01.81,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,so it's entirely feasible.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.23,0:07:03.58,Default,T,0,0,0,,Every month?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.58,0:07:06.48,Default,T,0,0,0,,And he always wins first \Nprize and runner up—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.36,0:07:11.61,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Well, Niizuma aside—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.61,0:07:16.04,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,In my opinion and according this report, \Nwhat you're lacking is a protagonist.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.04,0:07:18.16,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,A Jack-like protagonist that \Nreally draws people in.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.83,0:07:21.79,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll make the cut next \Ntime if you guys can create one.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.21,0:07:24.29,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,And you won't have to worry \Nabout Niizuma anymore either.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.54,0:07:28.17,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Niizuma Eiji's already getting \Nready for serialization,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.17,0:07:29.76,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,and we're still—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.76,0:07:33.80,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Last time, I told you guys I wanted \Nto submit your work for Next,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.80,0:07:36.01,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,but I think you should win \Nthe monthly prize first.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.01,0:07:40.31,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Because if you win, that work \Nwill be your debut piece.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.31,0:07:40.73,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.48,0:07:44.81,Default,S,0,0,0,,Is that the fastest way to get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.23,0:07:50.61,Default,S,0,0,0,,If we created a manuscript \Nwith serialization in mind,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.61,0:07:53.28,Default,S,0,0,0,,and it actually ended up \Nbeing serialization-level,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.28,0:07:54.95,Default,S,0,0,0,,would you let us get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.95,0:07:56.95,Default,T,0,0,0,,Saiko! We're not at—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.54,0:08:09.42,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I wouldn't mind, but you'd need to \Nhave at least three chapters drawn.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.42,0:08:12.34,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,And they'd have to be \Nmanuscripts, not just names—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.34,0:08:14.39,Default,S,0,0,0,,And if it was good enough, \Nwe could get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.51,0:08:19.39,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter how good it is, \Nif they don't even read it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.72,0:08:22.35,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,It might not even make it \Nto a serialization meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.35,0:08:24.81,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,It might be torn to shreds 'cause \Nthey think you're cocky—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.81,0:08:26.19,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.90,0:08:29.82,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Editor in Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.36,0:08:33.45,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,H—He's the Editor in Chief?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.90,0:08:35.82,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,A manga just needs to be good.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.49,0:08:38.70,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Good works will be serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.70,0:08:39.37,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.45,0:08:45.04,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,But your work isn't good.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.42,0:08:49.80,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,At your level, serialization is still impossible.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.88,0:08:52.34,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,It needs to be good.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.80,0:08:54.97,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Good works will be serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.59,0:08:59.39,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Those were Kawaguchi Taro's last words to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.14,0:09:02.06,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,He knows who I am?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.68,0:09:08.15,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's what Kawaguchi said when his \Ntermination from the company was announced.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.56,0:09:10.40,Default,T,0,0,0,,Termination from the company?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.11,0:09:15.49,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Authors serialized at Jack have \Nan annual contract salary.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.49,0:09:17.49,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Is it okay to tell them this?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.03,0:09:20.99,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,They really want to be pros, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.99,0:09:23.12,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Then there's no reason to hide the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.00,0:09:27.63,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,The pay isn't very high but just think of \Nit like a baseball player's annual salary.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.58,0:09:35.47,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Each year, the salary and page rate are determined \Nby how much their work contributed to Jack's success.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.38,0:09:41.35,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,But if the series ends and they can't \Ncome up with anything else that's good,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.35,0:09:43.97,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,we tell them, "You're no longer needed at Jack."
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.43,0:09:46.02,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,And their contract is terminated.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.98,0:09:50.86,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Kawaguchi came to this point,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.86,0:09:56.03,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,and as the Vice Editor in Chief, \NI had to break the news to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.66,0:09:59.99,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.74,0:10:05.45,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,So it's come to this.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.62,0:10:09.63,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Your Super Hero Legends was—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.63,0:10:12.25,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,It's alright, you don't need to say all that.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.25,0:10:16.01,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,It's been seven years and I haven't done \Na thing worth mentioning since then.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.01,0:10:16.72,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's not—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.38,0:10:18.97,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,This is easier on me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.97,0:10:22.01,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,I'll start from scratch and \Nsubmit works like the rookies.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.43,0:10:24.22,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,A manga just needs to be good.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.72,0:10:27.23,Default,Kawaguchi,0,0,0,,Good works will be serialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.81,0:10:32.61,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,After that, he brought in works one by \None, without caring what he looked like.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.98,0:10:36.78,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,He continued to bring in manuscripts, not \Nnames, until five days before he died.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.28,0:10:47.41,Default,S,0,0,0,,Um— Is it true Niizuma Eiji's \Npreparing to get serialized?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.29,0:10:49.92,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.25,0:10:54.09,Default,S,0,0,0,,What's the biggest difference \Nbetween us and Niizuma?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.92,0:11:00.76,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,To put it simply: how much you love manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.34,0:11:03.97,Default,T,0,0,0,,We love manga too.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.97,0:11:05.10,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,I can tell.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.97,0:11:09.35,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,But he does to an extraordinary extent.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.35,0:11:12.94,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,He picked up a pen at age six and \Nhasn't stopped drawing since.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.61,0:11:18.82,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Even when I went to go visit him, \Nhe never once put down his pen.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.32,0:11:24.28,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Drawing manga is like breathing \Nto him, practically involuntary.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.16,0:11:30.46,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,I think he'll get continue to improve \Nwhether he's serialized or not.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.17,0:11:33.92,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,But he can probably never be number one.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.92,0:11:35.13,Default,T,0,0,0,,He can't be number one?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.59,0:11:39.38,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,He has energy but no depth, \Nbecause he's young.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.38,0:11:40.89,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Children might enjoy his works,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.89,0:11:44.55,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,but our target readers, middle and high \Nschool students, will expect something more.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.55,0:11:45.55,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.55,0:11:46.60,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.60,0:11:50.89,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Considering their age, the work these \Ntwo produce is very deep and complex.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.89,0:11:53.31,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Yes, but some parts are too complex—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.27,0:11:55.27,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,The depth—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.94,0:11:57.02,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,The content—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.53,0:12:01.36,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Takagi, Mashiro, just bring in names from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.36,0:12:05.32,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Just focus on finding a charismatic, \NJack-like protagonist and keep bringing works in!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.95,0:12:09.83,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Then we can decide together which \Nones you should draw out in full.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.83,0:12:10.87,Default,T,0,0,0,,Just names?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.21,0:12:15.75,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Yes. Mashiro's art will get better with \Npractice, and it's already pretty good.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.75,0:12:17.21,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,We need to focus on the content now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.75,0:12:21.13,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,This way, you guys can aim directly for Next.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.13,0:12:23.51,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Good, Hattori. You can evaluate their names.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.09,0:12:27.14,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Create a good piece with Hattori first.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.14,0:12:29.56,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's the fastest way to serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.22,0:12:31.02,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,How's that sound?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.31,0:12:33.10,Default,S&T,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.69,0:12:40.19,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Chief, why'd you bring up Taro \NKawaguchi all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.24,0:12:44.66,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,I had a hunch, seeing Mashiro's \Nlast name and address.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.20,0:12:47.45,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,He's Kawaguchi Taro's nephew.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.91,0:12:50.08,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,He taught Mashiro?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.79,0:12:51.91,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Yeah—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.29,0:12:54.87,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,But you'd never guess that.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.67,0:13:01.42,Default,T,0,0,0,,Getting our names evaluated is \Nanother step forward, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.38,0:13:03.34,Default,S,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.15,0:13:19.27,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,Create a good piece with Hattori first.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.40,Default,Editor,0,0,0,,That's the fastest way to serialization.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.78,0:13:23.28,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Just bring in names from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.28,0:13:26.91,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Then we can decide together which \Nones you should draw out in full.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.91,0:13:29.58,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,I'm feeling more pressure now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.16,0:13:32.62,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,But Hattori believes in us.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.25,0:13:34.16,Default,S,0,0,0,,Huh—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.12,0:13:37.54,Default,S,0,0,0,,Shuujin, you're here al—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.54,0:13:37.88,Default,S,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.09,0:13:42.00,Default,S,0,0,0,,Shuujin.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.00,0:13:43.67,Default,T,0,0,0,,Hey Saiko.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.67,0:13:44.67,Default,T,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.89,0:13:49.05,Default,T,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.47,0:13:50.55,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.55,0:13:53.64,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Just 'cause we were here alone, doesn't \Nmean we were doing anything weird!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.64,0:13:55.73,Default,S,0,0,0,,That's not the issue.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.56,0:13:59.44,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I only realized after she got here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.44,0:14:00.11,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.77,0:14:04.61,Default,T,0,0,0,,I told you this place belonged to \NMashiro's uncle, a mangaka, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.61,0:14:06.11,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Yeah, and?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.07,0:14:09.70,Default,T,0,0,0,,Saiko doesn't want Azuki to know about this.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.70,0:14:11.99,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Why not? It doesn't matter, does it?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.99,0:14:14.04,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Not like you're doing something bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.04,0:14:16.21,Default,S,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I just—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.21,0:14:18.21,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's pride or something—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.21,0:14:19.54,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's complicated.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.54,0:14:21.21,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Pride, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.21,0:14:24.00,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,I heard it all from Miho by the way.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.00,0:14:27.63,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,It's super weird to "support each other until \Nyou both succeed and not truly date until then."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.97,0:14:29.97,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,And after you succeed, you'll get married?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.14,0:14:34.97,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,I can't believe Azuki told Miyoshi everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.35,0:14:36.06,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.77,0:14:39.19,Default,S,0,0,0,,Nothing. It has nothing to do with you, anyways.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.19,0:14:40.15,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,It definitely does!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.15,0:14:42.19,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,She's my best friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.19,0:14:45.15,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,It's almost Christmas! You two are slacking!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.15,0:14:46.07,Default,T,0,0,0,,Who are you calling?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.07,0:14:47.78,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Miho, who else?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.78,0:14:49.53,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Miho?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.53,0:14:51.74,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,I'm with Takagi and Mashiro right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.74,0:14:53.37,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Why don't you come over and the four of us can—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.49,0:14:53.37,Default-Alt2,S,0,0,0,,Wait, sto—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.24,0:14:56.29,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,She said no.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.20,0:15:01.33,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Azuki and I can't do stuff like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.67,0:15:03.63,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Why can't she understand?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.63,0:15:07.17,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,I know Miho's easily embarrassed and a little naive,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.17,0:15:09.68,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,but it's really hard to tolerate this.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.68,0:15:13.26,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Deciding to get married once your dreams \Ncome true when we're still in ninth grade?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.26,0:15:15.39,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Should we be making promises like that already?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.10,0:15:18.31,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Are you thinking about marrying me?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.31,0:15:18.93,Default,T,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.77,0:15:24.90,Default,T,0,0,0,,W—Why'd you—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.90,0:15:27.15,Default,T,0,0,0,,I was agreeing with what you were just saying!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.15,0:15:29.28,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,You answered way too quick.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.28,0:15:31.11,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Plus you said "not at all."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.91,0:15:33.37,Default,T,0,0,0,,Miyoshi—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.37,0:15:35.74,Default,T,0,0,0,,That's something that Saiko and \NAzuki decided for themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.74,0:15:37.33,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's not your place to interfere.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.16,0:15:40.66,Default,T,0,0,0,,I kind of understand their feelings.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.66,0:15:42.37,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's nice to be an idealist.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.75,0:15:47.55,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Then what would you do if I said I wouldn't \Nsee you until you became a mangaka?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.63,0:15:51.47,Default,T,0,0,0,,I can't answer that.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.47,0:15:52.59,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.59,0:15:55.43,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,That means it's something that'd \Nmake me kick you again, right?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.43,0:15:58.18,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,So something like, "That'd be annoying" \Nor "I wouldn't care" isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.06,0:16:00.68,Default,T,0,0,0,,Saiko! Help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.68,0:16:02.52,Default,S,0,0,0,,Alright, quit it already.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.98,0:16:07.77,Default,S,0,0,0,,Anyway, Miyoshi, you absolutely \Ncannot tell Azuki about this place.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.77,0:16:10.11,Default,T,0,0,0,,If you tell her, I'll break up with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.03,0:16:13.28,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Got it. I won't.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.28,0:16:16.78,Default,S,0,0,0,,And you, Shuujin, don't bring \NMiyoshi here without asking first.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.78,0:16:18.12,Default,T,0,0,0,,Sorry. Understood.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.12,0:16:19.20,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.20,0:16:22.50,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,But you two are always locked in \Nhere writing manga, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.50,0:16:24.46,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,We can't even go on dates on the weekends!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.46,0:16:27.50,Default,T,0,0,0,,You were the one who said that was okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.50,0:16:28.92,Default,T,0,0,0,,Don't make me keep reminding you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.92,0:16:30.09,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,But—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.09,0:16:32.26,Default,S,0,0,0,,Fine, if it's a holiday, you can come.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.76,0:16:34.76,Default,S,0,0,0,,On school days, you can see him at school.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.76,0:16:36.85,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Really? Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.18,0:16:38.89,Default,S,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.89,0:16:42.35,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Nothing. Just thinking you're \Npretty cute when I look closely,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.35,0:16:44.27,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Miho has good taste!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.81,0:16:46.19,Default,S,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.02,0:16:48.11,Default,T,0,0,0,,Hachiouji?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.11,0:16:52.15,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,Or something like that. Miho's probably \Ngoing to a private, all-girls school there.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.15,0:16:55.16,Default,T,0,0,0,,But Hachiouji's pretty far from here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.16,0:16:57.62,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,It's close to her lessons and \Nthe production company though.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.24,0:17:04.04,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,After entering high school, they might promote her \Nas an actress first, before getting into voice acting.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.04,0:17:05.04,Default,T,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.04,0:17:07.25,Default,T,0,0,0,,She wouldn't do something like \Nswimsuit shoots, would she?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.63,0:17:09.29,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,I'm not sure—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.29,0:17:11.26,Default,Kaya,0,0,0,,But as her boyfriend, you wouldn't want that, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.01,0:17:14.88,Default,S,0,0,0,,Azuki'd never do something like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.97,0:17:18.22,Default,S,0,0,0,,Come on Shuujin, let's get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:32.44,Notebook,,0,0,0,,{\frz5\blur1.003\1c&H4F4E4C&\pos(594.667,243.341)}Hachio
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.44,0:17:32.48,Notebook,,0,0,0,,{\frz5\blur1.003\1c&H4F4E4C&\pos(594.667,243.341)\clip(m 500 270.125 l 622.625 252.75 b 648.625 234 712.625 209.875 740 203.25 l 474.625 197.875)}Hachio
