Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.70,0:18:22.28,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,They're all terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.28,0:18:23.45,Default,S&T,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.79,0:18:24.91,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.91,0:18:27.66,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Every protagonist is now done in classic Jack style—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.59,0:18:37.51,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I got it! They're too ordinary.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.88,0:18:39.89,Default,T,0,0,0,,Too ordinary?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.34,0:18:44.01,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,They're all so Jack-like, none of \Nthem leave a lasting impression.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.56,0:18:46.77,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,In your attempt to make the \Nprotagonist more Jack-like,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.77,0:18:48.77,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,your story's been negatively affected.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.39,0:18:52.94,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Forget Niizuma Eiji, these works \Nwould lose to other rookies as well!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.94,0:18:53.77,Default,T,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.11,0:18:56.90,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I apologize. Looks like this \Nwas the wrong approach.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.90,0:18:59.78,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,It's clear you two aren't cut out \Nfor classic mainstream manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.78,0:19:00.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.91,0:19:03.28,Default,T,0,0,0,,But isn't that a fatal flaw for us?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.28,0:19:05.37,Default,S,0,0,0,,What should we do now?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.09,0:19:18.34,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,We're told our works won't sell in Jack—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.13,0:19:21.55,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Then we're told our works are too Jack-like to be in Jack—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.51,0:19:25.76,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Where does that leave us?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.85,0:19:29.77,Default,S,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.03,0:19:38.24,Default,S,0,0,0,,From Hattori?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.24,0:19:39.49,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.49,0:19:41.49,Default,T,0,0,0,,He wanted to know if we could \Nstop by after school today.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.84,0:19:42.74,Default,T,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 2,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.16,Yueisha,,0,0,0,,{\frz-30\fax0.6\blur0.869\move(720,280.778,777.333,280.778,0,3737)}Yueisha
Dialogue: 1,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.16,Yueisha,,0,0,0,,{\frz-30\fax0.6\1c&HF5EEEC&\blur0.869\move(722,278.104,779.333,278.104,0,3737)}Yueisha
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.16,Yueisha,,0,0,0,,{\frz-30\fax0.6\1c&H181818&\alpha&H80\blur0.869\move(718,282.783,775.333,282.783,0,3737)}Yueisha
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.54,0:19:49.16,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.42,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Sorry for calling you out all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.42,0:19:52.83,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's alright.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.83,0:19:54.58,Default,S,0,0,0,,Thanks for meet—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.58,0:19:57.13,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Let's not waste time. Do you \Nguys know about reader's surveys?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.84,0:19:59.67,Default,S,0,0,0,,Yeah, we know about them.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.67,0:20:03.72,Default,T,0,0,0,,They're a postcard that comes with Jack, \Nasking readers to rank their favorite works.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.72,0:20:04.09,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.76,0:20:08.81,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Truth be told, if 2 people out of 10 \Npick your work, it's considered a hit.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.81,0:20:09.73,Default,T,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.73,0:20:10.68,Default,S,0,0,0,,Only two?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.68,0:20:12.56,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Yes, you only need 20%.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.48,0:20:14.65,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Why'd he bring this up all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.65,0:20:16.44,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,Why's he being so frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:20.44,Survey,,0,0,0,,{\t(\fscy110\fscx110)\frz-18\blur1.003\move(706,193.87,710,175.82,0,4030)}Telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:20.44,Survey,,0,0,0,,{\t(\fscy110\fscx110)\frz-18\blur1.003\move(713.333,386.404,719.333,389.078,0,4030)}Age
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:20.44,Survey,,0,0,0,,{\t(\fscy110\fscx110)\frz-20\blur1.003\move(442.667,340.944,420,339.607,0,4030)}Boy\N\N\NGirl
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.86,0:20:20.44,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Takagi's strong point is the depth \Nand maturity of his stories.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.86,0:20:23.28,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I tried to combine that skill \Nwith mainstream devices,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.28,0:20:26.20,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,but instead ended up killing it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.08,0:20:28.24,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Change of plans.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.12,0:20:30.83,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Instead of trying to create a \Nwork that everyone will like,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.83,0:20:33.37,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,try to create a work that more \Nthan 50% of people will like.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.37,0:20:37.00,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,A work that 2 out of every 10 \Npeople will definitely love.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.34,0:20:41.01,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,If Niizuma's going through the front door, \Nthis would be called a backdoor route.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.01,0:20:42.59,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I want us to aim for such a piece.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.01,0:20:48.14,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Strictly speaking, Next has fewer \Nworks than a regular Jack edition.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.14,0:20:49.39,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,So 20% there isn't good enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.93,0:20:53.77,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,But a piece that could get 20% in our regular \Nedition would definitely have good results.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.77,0:20:54.98,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Actually, even if you do it in Next—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.98,0:20:57.94,Default-Italic,S,0,0,0,,A backdoor route—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.11,0:21:00.90,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,This is an all-or-nothing gamble!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.61,0:21:04.32,Default,T,0,0,0,,Please go into the details!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.74,0:21:11.50,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Were there any names you cut 'cause you thought \N"It won't sell in Jack" or "Readers won't like it?"
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.58,0:21:20.00,Default,T,0,0,0,,A popular high school boy tries to see how \Nmany girls he can cheat on at the same time.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.00,0:21:21.71,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's it! Stories like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.71,0:21:22.63,Default,T,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.63,0:21:25.93,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Most people would be turned off, \Nbut there's bound to be fans of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.72,0:21:28.35,Default,S,0,0,0,,What about that one, Shuujin?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.35,0:21:30.93,Default,S,0,0,0,,The one where you advance by \Nbuying what's in other people's brains.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.93,0:21:33.18,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's terrible, but great!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.18,0:21:34.39,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Tell me more about it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.39,0:21:38.69,Default,T,0,0,0,,You know how cell phones exchange \Ninformation through infrared, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.36,0:21:42.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,In the future, this'll be possible with people's \N brains, so anyone can buy or sell knowledge.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.78,0:21:48.20,Default,T,0,0,0,,Of course, intelligent people's minds would \Nbe more expensive 'cause they're worth more.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.20,0:21:49.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,You need money in order to buy information,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.91,0:21:52.83,Default,T,0,0,0,,so you'd sell your knowledge \Nto as many people as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.37,0:21:56.62,Default,T,0,0,0,,Less intelligent people will advance if you sell to them.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.62,0:21:59.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,So if you have to sell, sell to \Nsomeone as stupid as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.29,0:22:02.71,Default,T,0,0,0,,And if you wanna buy, buy from \Nsomeone as intelligent as possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.71,0:22:05.22,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's it! That would definitely do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.22,0:22:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.01,0:22:08.26,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,Why didn't you bring that one with you today?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.14,Default,T,0,0,0,,I just didn't think it was—
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.14,0:22:12.10,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,What's its title?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.10,0:22:15.73,Default,T,0,0,0,,Maybe it's bad taste, but it's "Money and \NIntelligence Make the World Go Round."
Dialogue: 10,0:22:16.06,0:22:17.69,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,That's perfect. Let's go with that!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.85,0:22:22.40,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,This is the only way to allow your \Nindividuality to shine through.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.15,0:22:25.61,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,I want to publish your works!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.57,0:22:29.70,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,So let us work on a name together,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.70,0:22:33.74,Default,Hattori,0,0,0,,and make the February 13th Jack Next deadline!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.13,0:22:41.96,Default,S&T,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
